title: Yankees-Orioles game called by rain; will play 2 on Saturday
text:
Yankees-Orioles game called by rain; will play 2 on Saturday Associated Press | 0 comments 
BALTIMORE (AP) â€” The game Friday between the New York Yankees and the Baltimore Orioles has been postponed by rain. 
The game will be made up as part of a split doubleheader Saturday. Starting times are 12:05 p.m. and 7:05 p.m. 
Hurricane Joaquin may have a say in that, as rain is expected in the area on Saturday. 
The Yankees arrived in town after clinching an AL wild-card berth with a 4-1 win over Boston on Thursday night. It was the franchise's 10,000th regular-season victory. 
This three-game series between AL East rivals runs through Sunday. The Yankees open postseason play Tuesday with a winner-take-all, wild-card matchup. 
Baltimore was eliminated from contention earlier this week. The Orioles need a three-game sweep to avoid a losing season.
